      <ExpenseAmt>32657386</ExpenseAmt>
      <RevenueAmt>38355422</RevenueAmt>
      <Desc>AS ONE OF SAN DIEGO'S LARGEST RESOURCES FOR INDIVIDUALS AND FAMILIES IMPACTED BY SUBSTANCE USE AND CO-OCURRING HEALTH CONDITIONS, MCALISTER INSTITUTE OFFERS A FULL CONTINUUM OF SUBSTANCE USE DISORDER TREATMENT FOR INDIVIDUALS ACROSS THE LIFESPAN THAT INCLUDES SCREENING AND ASSESSMENT, INDIVIDUAL AND GROUP COUNSELING, FAMILY THERAPY, CASE MANAGEMENT, TREATMENT PLANNING, HOUSING SUPPORTS, LINKAGES TO PHYSICAL HELATH, CO-OPERATIVE DAY CARE, REUNIFICATION SUPPORT, AND RECOVERY SERVICES. THIS INCLUDES 10 OUTPATIENT PROGRAMS, 4 RESIDENTIAL PROGRAMS, AND 2 DETOXIFICATION PROGRAMS THAT SERVED A TOTAL OF 6,219 INDIVIDUALS AND FAMILIES LAST YEAR.</Desc>
      <ProgSrvcAccomActy2Grp>
