        <Desc>2,102 INDIVIDUALS AND FAMILIES RECEIVED PREVENTION, EDUCATION, SCREENING, BRIEF INTERVENTION, STABILIZATION, DIVERSION, AND/OR OTHER SUPPORTIVE SERVICES TO ADDRESS NEEDS RELATED TO ALCOHOL AND OTHER DRUGS.</Desc>
      </ProgSrvcAccomActy2Grp>
