        <ExplanationTxt>THE ORGANIZATION HAS A WRITTEN CONFLICT OF INTEREST POLICY REQUIRING ACKNOWLEDGEMENT BY AND OFFICERS AND DIRECTORS TO IMMEDIATELY DISCLOSE ANY CONFLICTS OF INTEREST TO THE ORGANIZATION.</ExplanationTxt>
      </SupplementalInformationDetail>
      <SupplementalInformationDetail>
        <FormAndLineReferenceDesc>FORM 990, PAGE 6, PART VI, LINE 15A</FormAndLineReferenceDesc>
        <ExplanationTxt>THE ORGANIZATION HAS A INDEPENDENT COMPENSATION COMMITTEE OF THE BOARD OF DIRECTORS THAT REVIEWS AND DETERMINES THE COMPENSATION OF THE EXECUTIVE AND FINANCE DIRECTORS OF THE ORGANIZATION. THE COMPENSATION COMMITTEE OBTAINS INFORMATION REGARDING COMPARABLE COMPENSATION OF SIMILAR POSITIONS IN THE SOUTHERN CALIFORNIA AREA IN DETERMINING COMPENSATION FOR THE KEY OFFICERS AND MANAGEMENT PERSONNEL OF THE ORGANIZATION. MEMBERS OF THE BOARD OF DIRECTORS ARE NOT COMPENSATED.</ExplanationTxt>
      </SupplementalInformationDetail>
      <SupplementalInformationDetail>
        <FormAndLineReferenceDesc>FORM 990, PAGE 6, PART VI, LINE 15B</FormAndLineReferenceDesc>
        <ExplanationTxt>THE COMPENSATION COMMITTEE OBTAINS INFORMATION REGARDING COMPARABLE COMPENSATION OF SIMILAR POSITIONS IN THE SOUTHERN CALIFORNIA AREA IN DETERMINING COMPENSATION FOR THE KEY OFFICERS AND MANAGEMENT PERSONNEL OF THE ORGANIZATION.</ExplanationTxt>
